gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 110, Kings 98
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Kings, 110-98. Anthony Edwards led the way for the Timberwolves with 34 points, five rebounds and 10 assists, while Rudy Gobert added 21 points and 17 rebounds in the victory. Domantas Sabonis tallied 17 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists for the Kings in the losing effort, his fifth triple-double of the season and 37th of his career. The Timberwolves have won back-to-back games as they improve to 22-6 on the season, while the Kings fall to 17-11.
